## Context
Audit of scripts/ directory found 9 scripts with no Makefile wrapper and
2 scripts missing executable permissions.

## Problem
Running scripts required knowing exact paths and interpreters. No single
entry point for `gmake help` to surface them.

## Resolution
- Added 9 Makefile targets wrapping each unwrapped script
- Added help text under new "Scripts:" section in `gmake help`
- chmod +x generate-showcase.scm, generate-synthetic-session.py

## Result
- All 15 executable scripts now have Makefile targets
- `gmake lint` passes (0 errors, 2 warnings — both pre-existing)
- All shell scripts pass `bash -n` syntax check
- doc-check.sh: PASS | lint-contracts.sh: PASS | generate-test-pii.py: valid JSON
